title: Add support for customized color projections (fix #3)
body:
Restructured the relationship between `ColorPlaneScale$map_df` and projection functions to make a simple interface for user-defined projections. Added additional projections and customization options:
- Ability to specify the projection function to use in `scale_*_colorplane` scale constructors via the `color_projection` argument
- Color projection function to create custom gradient palettes: `interpolate_projection`
- Simple color projection preset based on the interpolate function: `red_blue_projection`
- Pass through of additional arguments to the scale constructors down to the projection functions, including `Y` to specify luminosity in `YUV` projections

title: Internalize unexported objects from ggplot2
body:
The package now gets a clean bill from R CMD check
1. Copied source code for internal functions and objects used from ggplot2
2. Turns out ggplot2 will pass along new aesthetics by default, no need to alter `ggplot2:::.all_aesthetics`
3. Removed changes to `ggplot2:::.base_to_ggplot` and instead added handling for "color2" alias to "colour2" aesthetic in the scale trainer
